Let me analyze the target structure and provide a solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure consists of 4 blocks in total
- It has 2 layers:
  * Bottom layer: Has a vertical orange cylindrical block with two triangular/wedge-shaped blocks on either side
  * Top layer: Has a red U-shaped block sitting on top of the cylinder

From the Block Dictionary:
- The red U-shaped top piece matches block #3
- The central vertical cylinder matches block #7
- The side wedges match blocks #14 and #16

Assembly Order:
The logical assembly sequence would be:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 7 (place the central cylinder)
    Step2: Move block with index 14 (place the left wedge)
    Step3: Move block with index 16 (place the right wedge)
    Step4: Move block with index 3 (place the red U-shaped top piece)
}

This will create the exact structure shown in the target image, with all blocks in their correct orientations without any need for rotation.
